			<item>
				<title>Rerank EndeavourOS mirrors</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/rerank-endeavouros-mirrors/</link>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:23:33 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/rerank-endeavouros-mirrors/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;To rerank Arch mirrors, follow &lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/rerank-arch-mirrors/&#34;&gt;this guide&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endeavour OS&lt;/strong&gt; has its own distro-unique packages, which may be slightly modified versions of Arch packages.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Update the Endeavour OS &lt;code&gt;mirrorlist&lt;/code&gt; with:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ eos-rankmirrors&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;The &lt;code&gt;eos-rankmirrors&lt;/code&gt; process only shows terminal output (no GUI tool).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The terminal may display errors/warnings as the system tests various mirrors for connectivity and speed. It may take a few minutes to find the requisite amount of mirrors.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Rerank Arch mirrors</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/rerank-arch-mirrors/</link>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:00:22 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/rerank-arch-mirrors/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;To rerank EndeavourOS mirrors, follow &lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/rerank-endeavouros-mirrors/&#34;&gt;this guide&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#common-issues-outdated-mirrors&#34;&gt;Common issues: outdated mirrors&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mirrors&lt;/strong&gt; are servers located around the world that store copies of software packages.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;When upgrading packages, your EndeavourOS system utilizes multiple mirrors, which are noted in a &lt;code&gt;mirrorlist&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A well-maintained &lt;code&gt;mirrorlist&lt;/code&gt; ensures the &lt;code&gt;pacman&lt;/code&gt; package manager can access up-to-date package files when performing system updates. Outdated mirrors can prevent &lt;code&gt;pacman&lt;/code&gt; from updating &lt;strong&gt;core packages&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;It is recommended to rerank mirrors at least every 1-2 months for an up-to-date mirrorlist.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Change default kernel</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/change-default-kernel/</link>
				<pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 16:58:36 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/change-default-kernel/</guid>
				<description>&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Note: This guide was originally published on &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/redzhift/mywiki/wiki/Change-default-kernel&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; and is also available in &lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/~jcho/pages/10649618/Change+default+kernel+at+boot&#34;&gt;Confluence&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;contents&#34;&gt;Contents&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#1-find-kernel-id-with-bootctl&#34;&gt;Find kernel id with &lt;code&gt;bootctl&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#2-edit-boot-loader-config&#34;&gt;Edit boot loader config&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#3-verify-and-reboot&#34;&gt;Verify and reboot&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#additional-information&#34;&gt;Additional information&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Your system can have multiple kernels (or installations) of the same Linux distro. This is typically from having different ISO images, such as EOS Mercury, Titan, and Ganymede. The newest kernel is usually booted by default, but can be adjusted to user preference.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Downgrade to specific date</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/downgrade-to-specific-date/</link>
				<pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2026 16:58:36 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/downgrade-to-specific-date/</guid>
				<description>&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Note: This guide was originally published on &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/redzhift/mywiki/wiki/Downgrade-to-specific-date&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; and is also available in &lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/~jcho/pages/10321937/Downgrade+package+to+specific+date&#34;&gt;Confluence&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;downgrade-packages-with-eos-shifttime&#34;&gt;Downgrade packages with &lt;code&gt;eos-shifttime&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;eos-shifttime&lt;/code&gt; application can revert system packages to their state at a specified date. This tool is useful for when recent updates cause issues with system or program functionalities.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open a terminal window and run &lt;code&gt;eos-shifttime&lt;/code&gt; with root permissions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Select the date to revert to on the GUI window, then click &lt;strong&gt;Revert&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/images/eos-shifttime.png&#34; alt=&#34;A GUI window for the eos-shifttime tool displaying a monthly calendar. The selected date is January 2, 2026.&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Update with pacman</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/update-pacman/</link>
				<pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 14:09:31 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/update-pacman/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;Arch systems should be updated daily to weekly. There are 3 commands used to Endeavour OS: &lt;code&gt;pacman -Syu&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;yay&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;eos-update&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#sudo-pacman--syu&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;pacman -Syu&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#yay&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;yay&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#eos-update&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;eos-update&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;pacman--syu&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;pacman -Syu&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To perform a full system update and refresh, run:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ sudo pacman -Syu&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;pacman&lt;/code&gt; is the package manager used to install and update programs in Arch Linux.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Some commands require appending &lt;code&gt;sudo&lt;/code&gt; to them - this is because they require &lt;strong&gt;root permissions&lt;/strong&gt;. These elevated permissions allows the &lt;code&gt;su&lt;/code&gt;peruser to &lt;code&gt;do&lt;/code&gt; system-related tasks, such as updating the computer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
